#Functions

    a function is a named sequence of statements that performed a computation.
    You can "call" the function by name.

Example : type(32)

    type is the name,() in the parentheis is called #argument#
    we say the function takes argument and return a result.

Type converting , Math function...


Composition  combine all the elements(variable, expression, statements)

Definaton a Functions

    def , keyword
    header + body
    Header should end with a colon
    Define before use

Flow execution
    from top to bottom
    
